#### Describe the solution you'd like

The reason is that in createInstance instance function and context.request are not equal

This is the workaround I envisioned

- `lib/axios.js`

```js
function createInstance(defaultConfig) {
  const context = new Axios(defaultConfig);
  // -             bind(Axios.prototype.request, context);
  const instance = bind(context.request, context);
  // ...
  return instance;
}
```
However, this will cause nested references
```js
axios.request.request.request.request.request // fun
```
so it should be
```js
function createInstance(defaultConfig) {
  const context = new Axios(defaultConfig);
  function request(...args) { context.request(...args) }
  // -             bind(Axios.prototype.request, context);
  const instance = bind(request, context);
  // ...
  return instance;
}
```

