```
api.interceptors.use((next, config) => {

  // REQUEST changes here

  if (someError) {
    return Promise.reject("I known how to handle this error")
  }
  if (unnededRequest) {
    return Promise.resolve("Resolve without perform request")
  }

  return next(config)
    .then(/* RESPONSE changes here */)
    .catch(/* RESPONSE error handler here */)
})
```
This can be enhanced by using utilities functions instead of `Promise.reject`/`Promise.resolve` to return "templated" responses.

