### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.

We were on axios 0.25.0, using it for running TypeScript implemented AWS Lambda Functions on node,  building the Lambda Functions with AWS CDK, which uses esbuild (0.16.7) to do tree shaking.

When upgrading to axios 1.21.1 there was a great improvement of reducing file size with 90 kb for Lambda Functions that do not actually use axios (but had imports from files where functions with it was used).

Unfortunately, I was dismayed to see a substantial file size increase of 264 kb (10-35% for our project) for Lambda Functions that do use axios, which is most of them.

After rebuilding with several different axios versions, it seems axios 0.27.0 is the major culprit. Upgrading from 0.26.1 to 0.27.0 adds over 241 kb to the tree shaken (but not minified) build output file. That is a 17-32% file size increase in our project.
It's mostly caused by new dependencies:
* 3 KB delayed-stream
* 3 KB mime-types
* 5 KB combined-stream
* 6 KB asynckit
* 73 KB axios (up from 55 KB)
* 206 KB mime-db

The 0.25.0 to 1.21.1 breakdown:
* 2 KB proxy-from-en
* 3 KB delayed-stream
* 3 KB mime-types
* 5 KB combined-stream
* 6 KB asynckit
* 93 KB axios (up from 54 KB)
* 206 KB mime-db



### Describe the solution you'd like

Ensure import/export based tree shaking can remove mime-db, and preferable other libraries. Ideally, also look into why axios itself has increased so much.

### Describe alternatives you've considered

Rolling back axios version upgrade.

