### Describe the bug

A performance issue has been introduced in Axios 0.28.0 by https://github.com/axios/axios/pull/4871. This pull request has added the following utility function:

```javascript
function isEmptyObject(val) {
  return val && Object.keys(val).length === 0 && Object.getPrototypeOf(val) === Object.prototype;
}
```

Here, `Object.keys(val)` creates an array with with all the keys of `val`, which can be anything. In particular, if `val` is a string, `Object.keys(val)` creates an array which has the length of the string.

Each time a request is executed, `isEmptyObject()` may be called on its body, which can be very costly if the body is a large string.

I noticed this issue while using Axios to send large newline-delimited JSON POST requests (in order to bulk index documents to Elasticsearch). In this use case, the request body can have a length up to 10MB, and `isEmptyObject()` takes more than 1 second to execute on my laptop.

