When uploading a file with axios 1.7.0 and above with an `onUploadProgress` callback provided, the callback will get called ~2.5 times per second compared to ~5 (or even ~15 on a close server) times per second in axios 1.6.8.

### To Reproduce

Go to https://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/axios-slow-progress-1-7-3-3282wk, open console, click on upload, after waiting a bit you should see something like `Finished uploading file, axios made 2.28 progress reports per second` in the console.

### Code snippet

```js
// create a 50 MB file
const size = 50 * 1024 * 1024;
const chunkSize = 1024;
const uint8 = new Uint8Array(chunkSize);
let parts = [];
for (let i = 0; i < size; i += chunkSize) {
  parts.push(uint8);
}
const blob = new Blob(parts);
const file = new File([blob], "filename");

// upload the file and count how many progress events did we get
let count = 0;
const startTime = Date.now();
const formData = new FormData();
formData.append("file", file);
axios.post("https://httpbin.org/post", formData, {
  onUploadProgress: (e) => {
    console.log(`progress: ${e.progress}, count: ${count}`);
    count++;
    // NOTE: from 1.7.0 progress doesn't reach exactly 1, this is fixed in 1.7.3
    if (e.progress === 1) {
      const elapsedSecs = (Date.now() - startTime) / 1000;
      const reportsPerSec = Math.round((count / elapsedSecs) * 100) / 100;
      console.log(
        `Finished uploading file, axios made ${reportsPerSec} progress reports per second`
      );
    }
  },
});
```


