### Describe the bug

### Object subfield appears frozen while array element reflects later mutation

When using an async request interceptor that introduces a delay, mutating the original payload after calling axios.post(...) but before the actual network send results in inconsistent behavior:

A nested object (e.g., payload.object) appears frozen at its earlier state ("before"),
While an element inside an array (e.g., payload.array[0]) reflects the later mutation ("after").

This is surprising because both structures are part of the same payload and were mutated at the same time. The issue is not about immutability per se—we understand that Axios may serialize later due to async interceptors—but about inconsistency across sibling properties in the same payload.

### To Reproduce

Single file project that reproduce the issue : https://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/axiosobjectmutation-qsrp2n

### Code snippet

